    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-11-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-12-22T20:58:20Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to revise the tax credit for health insurance costs to: (1) extend such credit to employees of companies in bankruptcy reorganization; (2) decrease from 55 to 50 the age at which Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation pension recipients are eligible for such credit; (3) repeal the three-month existing coverage requirement; and (4) extend the credit to spouses of certain individuals eligible for such credit.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to provide that employees of certain companies seeking bankruptcy protection are eligible for the health coverage tax credit, and for other purposes.</title>
